node.text:
This is a perfect idea to make a delicious lunch for the whole family!

INGREDIENTS
500g minced meat
1 onion
1 egg
ham slices
Cheese slices
Grilled zucchini slices
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
3 eggs
Flour
Breadcrumbs

METHOD
Mix together minced meat with onion, egg, salt, and black pepper.
Spread the meat on cling film, top it with cherry slices, ham slices, and grilled zucchini. Wrap in a roll and freeze for 1 hour.
Cut into slices and dip into flour eggs and breadcrumbs.
Fry in the hot oil until golden brown.

You won't be able to stop at one!

INGREDIENTS
300g hazelnut cream
120ml (½ cup) milk
7g dry yeast
50g sugar
2 eggs
Oil
1 lime zest
260g (2 cups) flour
 
Sugar for coating
 
METHOD
Pour the hazelnut cream into small portions on the parchment paper. Leave in the freezer for 1-2 hours.
 
Dissolve the dry yeast and sugar in the milk. Add the eggs, oil, lime zest, flour and mix well.
 
Take portions of the batter with a spoon and fill them with the cold hazelnut cream.
 
Fry the mixture in boiling oil until golden.
 
Dip the pancakes in sugar and serve.

Here're 2 amazing ideas with #tortilla!

INGREDIENTS
Tortillas
4 eggs
50g (1/2 cup) shredded cheese
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp pepper
1/3 red bell pepper
1/3 yellow pepper
1/3 green pepper
80ml (1/3 cup) sour cream
 
METHOD
Make circles on tortillas by using a glass or a plate. Transfer them to a baking pan.
Mix eggs with species and shredded cheese, pour the mixture into the tortilla cups, add chopped peppers.
Bake at 180’C (350’F) for 5 minutes, sprinkle with shredded cheese and bake for 4 minutes more.
Add egg mixture to a pan and cover with tortilla, fry from both sides. Wrap it in the roll.

Perfect for a tasty dinner, this #focaccia is ready in a few steps!

INGREDIENTS
60ml (1/4 cup) water
7g dry yeast
250g (2 cups) flour
8g (2 tsp) sugar
4g (1 tsp) salt
10ml (2 tsp) olive oil
120ml (½ cup) milk
Butter
Cheese

METHOD
In a small bowl, pour water, yeast, sugar, and a spoonful of flour.
Leave to rise for 15 minutes.
Pour flour, salt and yeast mixture into a mixing bowl. Add milk and knead the dough.
Drizzle the dough with oil and knead until combined. Leave to stand for 60 minutes.
Divide into four parts and fill with butter and cheese.
Bake in a pan. Serve.

With zucchini, eggs and potatoes you can make a delicious dinner in no-time! 
 
INGREDIENTS
3 medium potatoes
1 zucchini
2 eggs (1 for the omelette & 1 for the fritters)
6 g (1 tsp) salt
60 ml (4 tbsp) vegetable oil (divided, for frying)
2 g (2 tsp) parsley, chopped (divided, optional)
60g (2 oz) mozzarella, shredded

METHOD
Grate potatoes and zucchini and transfer to the strainer to remove any excess liquids.
Place strained flesh into a bowl and season with salt.
Add an egg and mix well.
Heat a tablespoon of oil in a frying pan. Place 3-4 tablespoons of potato-zucchini mixture and form a round fritter.
Cook it for 2-3 minutes or until golden, then flip and make a hole in the middle with a small spoon.
Add an egg into the hole. Cover with a lid and cook until the desired doneness of the egg yolk.
Season with salt and sprinkle chopped parsley on top (optional).
Add one more tablespoon of oil to the frying pan. Form small round fritters from the remaining mixture and cook on both sides until golden.
When almost cooked, top each fritter with shredded cheese, cover with a lid and cook on low until cheese melts.
Sprinkle some chopped parsley on top (optional) and serve immediately.

A tasty dinner idea qith #eggplants that everyone will love! 
 
INGREDIENTS
2 eggplants
100g mozzarella cheese
100g feta cheese
1/2 yellow bell pepper
1/2 red bell pepper
2 egg whites
2 egg yolks

METHOD
Cut off the top part of the eggplants. Spread them with oil and bake at 200°C (390°F) for 20 minutes.
Cut cheese and peppers.
Fill the eggplants with cheeses, pepper and egg whites, bake for 20 minutes more, add egg yolks on top and bake for 5 minutes.

Your guests will love these #appetizers!

1) Rolls
INGREDIENTS
Slices of salami
Cream cheese
Cherry tomatoes
Black olives
Green olives
 
METHOD
Form several rows of salami, placing one slice on top of the other on a piece of cling film. Add cream cheese and spread over all the salami.
In the first section add cherry tomatoes, in the middle green olives and black olives the last section. Carefully roll the salami up horizontally.
Refrigerate for two hours and then cut into pieces.
-------------------------------------------
2) Boats
INGREDIENTS
Salami
Black olives
Cream cheese
 
METHOD
Add a tablespoon of cream cheese to a slice of salami.
Place a black olive on top of the cream cheese and use a toothpick to form a boat.
-------------------------------------------
3) Cones
INGREDIENTS
Salami
Ricotta
Capers
 
METHOD
Place the ricotta cheese in a piping bag.
Roll a slice of salami into a cone shape and fill with the ricotta cheese. Decorate with capers.

You can make these treats at home in minutes!

INGREDIENTS
1 egg white
Lemon juice drops
150g powdered sugar
50g apricot jam
Puff pastry

METHOD
Cut a slice of puff pastry into several symmetrical rectangles. Arrange on a baking sheet neatly.
Beat the egg white, add a few drops of lemon juice, and gradually pour in icing sugar while whisking continually.
Brush the icing sugar mixture over each puff pastry rectangle.
Strain the jam to remove lumps, place it in a piping bag and decorate each rectangle. Bake at 180°C (356°F) for 20 minutes.

You won't be able to stop at one, these rolls are perfect for a tasty appetizer!

INGREDIENTS
Tramezzini
Cream cheese
Ham
Salame
Mayonnaise
Tuna

METHOD
Use a rolling pin to spread the tramezzini and make it thinner.
In first spread the cream cheese and add ham.
Second fill with cream cheese.
Third fill with mayonnaise and tuna.
Roll them and put in foil then refrigerate.
Cut them into slices and serve.

This is a perfect idea to make a delicious lunch for the whole family!

INGREDIENTS
500g minced meat
1 onion
1 egg
ham slices
Cheese slices
Grilled zucchini slices
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
3 eggs
Flour
Breadcrumbs

METHOD
Mix together minced meat with onion, egg, salt, and black pepper.
Spread the meat on cling film, top it with cherry slices, ham slices, and grilled zucchini. Wrap in a roll and freeze for 1 hour.
Cut into slices and dip into flour eggs and breadcrumbs.
Fry in the hot oil until golden brown.

This #cremecaramel is so mouth-watering, and you can make it in no time!

INGREDIENTS:
12g of hydrated gelatin
395g (1 1/3 cup) condensed milk
70g (4 tablespoons) of powdered milk
400ml (1 2/3 cup) of cooking cream
200ml (1 cup) of milk
Vanilla essence

Caramel sauce:
320g (2 cups) of sugar
200ml (1 cup) of water

METHOD
In a saucepan add the sugar and mix until dissolved. Add the water occasionally to create the caramel.
In a bowl add the cooking cream, milk, gelatin, condensed milk, powdered milk, and mix. Add the mixture into the blender and combine it all well together.
In plastic glasses add the first layer of the caramel and the white creme on top
Refrigerate four hours before serving. Take a glass and separate the caramel cream from the edges with a knife, turn the glass over and lift it.

This is the perfect idea to make a delicious #appetizer in a few steps!

INGREDIENTS
2 slices toast bread
4 small wurstels
12 slices cheese

METHOD
Cut each slice of bread into 3 pieces.
Place 2 wurstels between bread pieces.
Thread bread and wurstels onto 3 skewers and cut to obtain 3 separate skewers.
Heat up your crepe maker.
Arrange a cheese slice on top.
When the cheese begins to bubble, put one skewer onto the melted cheese. Cook for a few seconds, then flip it together with the cheese. Continue with the remaining skewers.
Arrange skewers on the plate and serve immediately.

node.text: They are ready in just a few minutes, using just a few ingredients. You won’t be able to eat only one! INGREDIENTS300g zucchinisalt150g flour2 eggs80g Parmesan cheese60ml milk8g instant yeastpepper DIRECTIONS1. Grate the zucchini, strain them and let them dry off for 15 minutes.2. Prepare the batter by combining the flour, eggs, Parmesan cheese, milk and yeast.3. Add the zucchini and pepper to the batter.4. Pour a spoonful of the batter into hot oil and let it cook for 2/3 minutes per side.5. Sprinkle with salt and serve hot.#cookistwow #cookistrecipe #recipes #cooking #food #foodie #instafood #foodlove #italianfood #yummy #dinner #lunch #food #yummy #instafood ##homemade #foodstagram #eat #instacake #instaphone #foodblogger #foodblog #Iovefood #instamood #instagood #bestoftheday #picoftheday

You won't be able to stop at one!

INGREDIENTS
300g hazelnut cream
120ml (½ cup) milk
7g dry yeast
50g sugar
2 eggs
Oil
1 lime zest
260g (2 cups) flour
 
Sugar for coating
 
METHOD
Pour the hazelnut cream into small portions on the parchment paper. Leave in the freezer for 1-2 hours.
 
Dissolve the dry yeast and sugar in the milk. Add the eggs, oil, lime zest, flour and mix well.
 
Take portions of the batter with a spoon and fill them with the cold hazelnut cream.
 
Fry the mixture in boiling oil until golden.
 
Dip the pancakes in sugar and serve.
